5 min\/100°F\/speed 3.5<b> while adding reserved ground sugar 1 tbsp at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid."},{"content":" <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Transfer whipped egg whites to a large bowl and carefully and slowly fold in 1 oz reserved ground hazelnuts, until just incorporated. Reserve remaining hazelnuts to garnish. Carefully spoon whipped egg mixture inside circles drawn on the parchment. Spread meringue to edges forming 12 meringue disks."},{"content":"Bake meringues for 10 minutes (300°F), reduce heat to 250°F and bake 60 minutes (250°F). Turn off oven and without opening oven door allow meringues to cool (approx. 2 hrs.). Meanwhile clean mixing bowl and make filling."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Rhubarb Compote and Whipped Cream Filling"},{"content":"Place sugar and orange peels into mixing bowl, insert measuring cup and grate <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Add cinnamon, star anise, nutmeg and 6 oz rhubarb and cook <b>5 min\/212°F\/\/speed 1<b>. Add remaining 6 oz rhubarb and cook <b>4 min\/175°F\/\/speed 1<b>. Refrigerate filling until cold, remove and discard cinnamon and star anise. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place whipping cream into mixing bowl and without measuring cup whip <b>speed 3.5<b> until cream is barely holding its shape (approx. 25 sec.). <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>."},{"content":"Sandwich two Hazelnut Meringues with Whipped Cream and Rhubarb Compote. Repeat with remaining meringues. Garnish with chopped hazelnuts, dust with confectioners sugar and serve immediately."}],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","4h","6 pieces"]}